[node name="PlayerSpawn" type="Marker3D" parent="."]
transform = Transform3D(1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 1.0, 8.5)

; Five cryo pods in a pentagon, centred on (0, 3) with a 2.9m radius, doors facing OUTWARD
; so each occupant steps into the room rather than into the middle of the ring.
;
; Only the +Z pod is the player's, and it faces aft — you wake looking back down the wake at
; where you came from, straight down the middle of the wide aft window. The other four are scenery and have
; `is_player_pod = false`, which stops them offering an identical prompt for a pod that does
; nothing. Rotation is 180 + i*72 degrees, which is what points each door away from centre.
; CD_CryoStation_v1 — a furnace, and what the pod ring is arranged around. The model is
; authored 6.6m across and 10.3m tall to the top of its flue; at 0.43 it is 2.84m wide and
; 4.43m tall, with about 11cm to each pod's back — they read as docked to it.
;
; The ring went back out from 2.6m to 2.9m to allow this. At 2.6m the only station that fit
; was 3.5m tall, which is SHORTER than the 3.25m pods once their own ceiling pipes are
; counted — it was completely enclosed and could not be seen from anywhere in the room. A
; prop nobody can see is not worth placing. At 2.9m the flue clears the pods by over a metre
; and the cluster still reads as tight.
[node name="CryoStation" parent="." instance=ExtResource("24_station")]
transform = Transform3D(0.43, 0, 0, 0, 0.43, 0, 0, 0, 0.43, 0, 0, 3)

