; The coolant loop gets the pipe instead of a flat panel: it is the fault whose patch costs
; air, so it is the one that most needs the player to SEE what they bought.
; The pipe is a floor-standing 3.5m column now rather than a panel on the wall, so it hangs
; off the malfunction node with no offset. Its rupture sits at about 1.7m, which is eye
; height — that matters, because a level look-ahead ray once sailed clean over the old
; waist-high pipe and it was visible but not targetable.
[node name="RepairPanel" parent="CoolantLoop" instance=ExtResource("21_pipe")]
patch_text = "Tape the split"
fit_text = "Fit a machined sleeve"

